# React / Next.js Rules

## Component model

- Functional components only. No class components.
- Server components by default. Add `"use client"` only when you need:
  - Browser APIs (`window`, `document`, etc.)
  - State or effects (`useState`, `useEffect`)
  - Event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`)
  - Framer Motion animations

## File organization

- One component per file. Filename matches component name (`HeroAnimation.tsx`).
- Colocate component-specific types in the same file.
- Shared types live in `src/types/`.

## Styling

- Tailwind only. No inline styles unless dynamic (e.g. animated SVG colors via props).
- For dynamic Tailwind classes, use the full class name — never string-interpolate (`bg-${color}` breaks JIT).

```tsx
// BAD
<div className={`bg-${color}-500`} />

// GOOD
const colorClasses = { red: 'bg-red-500', blue: 'bg-blue-500' };
<div className={colorClasses[color]} />
```

## Framer Motion

- Use `motion.svg`, `motion.path`, etc. directly — don't wrap.
- Prefer `variants` over inline `animate` props for anything beyond trivial transitions.
- All template animations should loop seamlessly (set `repeat: Infinity` and design the keyframes accordingly).

## Forms

- Controlled inputs only.
- Use native `<form>` with `action` for server actions when possible.
